def leafSimilar(root1, root2):
    def getLeaves(node):
        if not node:
            return []
        if not node.left and not node.right:
            return [node.val]
        return getLeaves(node.left) + getLeaves(node.right)

    return getLeaves(root1) == getLeaves(root2)
```

    The algorithm performs a depth-first search on both trees, collecting the leaf nodes' values and appending them into two arrays (leaves1 and leaves2). Once the values are collected, the arrays are compared to check if they are equal. If the arrays are equal, it returns true, meaning the trees are leaf-similar. Otherwise, it returns false. The getLeaves function is a recursive function that traverses the tree depth-wise and appends the leaf nodes' values to the array.

